The paper proposes a defense strategy for machine learning systems against adversarial attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of machine learning systems, which is a security concern, indicating that it could belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The proposed defense strategy involves a multi-channel architecture, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of a secret key, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.NE, in that order.
